Danish

MVC Mønster står for Model-View-Controller Mønster.
Dette mønster bruges til at adskille applikationens bekymringer.

Model - Model repræsenterer en genstand eller JAVA POJO bærer data.
Det kan også have logik at opdatere controlleren, hvis dens data ændres.

View - View repræsenterer visualisering af de data, som modellen indeholder.

Controller - Controller virker både på model og visning.
 Det styrer datastrømmen i modelobjekt og opdaterer visningen, når data ændres.
 Det holder visning og model adskilt.


English

MVC Pattern stands for Model-View-Controller Pattern.
This pattern is used to separate application's concerns.

Model - Model represents an object or JAVA POJO carrying data.
It can also have logic to update controller if its data changes.

View - View represents the visualization of the data that model contains.

Controller - Controller acts on both model and view.
 It controls the data flow into model object and updates the view whenever data changes.
 It keeps view and model separate.